  "root_text": {
    "iti66:0.1": "Itivuttaka 66 ",
    "iti66:0.2": "Tikanipāta ",
    "iti66:0.3": "Dutiyavagga ",
    "iti66:0.4": "Soceyyasutta ",
    "iti66:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti66:2.1": "“Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, soceyyāni. ",
    "iti66:2.2": "Katamāni tīṇi? ",
    "iti66:2.3": "Kāyasoceyyaṁ, vacīsoceyyaṁ, manosoceyyaṁ—",
    "iti66:2.4": "imāni kho, bhikkhave, tīṇi soceyyānī”ti. ",
    "iti66:2.5": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti66:2.6": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti66:3.1": "“Kāyasuciṁ vacīsuciṁ, ",
    "iti66:3.2": "cetosucimanāsavaṁ; ",
    "iti66:3.3": "Suciṁ soceyyasampannaṁ, ",
    "iti66:3.4": "āhu sabbappahāyinan”ti. ",
    "iti66:4.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti66:4.2": "Sattamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti66:0.1": "So It Was Said 66 ",
    "iti66:0.2": "The Book of the Threes ",
    "iti66:0.3": "Chapter Two ",
    "iti66:0.4": "Purity ",
    "iti66:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti66:2.1": "“Mendicants, there are these three kinds of purity. ",
    "iti66:2.2": "What three? ",
    "iti66:2.3": "Purity of body, speech, and mind. ",
    "iti66:2.4": "These are the three kinds of purity.” ",
    "iti66:2.5": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti66:2.6": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti66:3.1": "“Purity of body, purity of speech, ",
    "iti66:3.2": "and undefiled purity of heart. ",
    "iti66:3.3": "A pure one, blessed with purity, ",
    "iti66:3.4": "has given up everything, they say.” ",
    "iti66:4.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "iti66:3.1": "vacīsuciṁ → vācāsuciṁ (bj, sya-all, pts-vp-pli1, mr) ",
    "iti66:3.4": "āhu sabbappahāyinan”ti → āhu sabbapahāyinanti (sya-all, pts-vp-pli1); āhu ninhātapāpakanti (an3.121:1 [121. Dutiyasoceyyasutta]) "
  },
